{"TopicId":132725,"ForumId":50,"TopicTitle":"PSA Stable planes","CreatedByName":"Nich","CreatedById":145678,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-22T19:24:17Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Nich","CreatedById":145678,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-22T19:24:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf your like me you hate that stable planes dive into the ground. \u00A0Well I have finally figured out how to fix this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStart with putting on your main wing right at the COM\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/H9lccLe.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022H9lccLe.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen give it a positive AOI (angle of incidence). \u00A0The more AOI and the more wing/t you have the slower the plane will want fly straight and level\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/10gb4KV.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u002210gb4KV.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen add the tail elevators. \u00A0Give them a negative AOI until the COM and COL are dead centered.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/X4xoYpN.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022X4xoYpN.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis does a couple things that are VERY nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. If you are flying too slow your plane will dive to pick up speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. If you are flying too fast your plane will climb to shed\u00A0speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. When flying just right it will fly nice and level\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis makes SAS heading hold work much better. Currently SAS fights this diving tendency of stable planes however it is never really at the heading it wants to be so when you attempt to pull up just a little it resets it\u0027s heading lock which is now lower then the old heading lock and the plane dives further.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the plane is too stable simply move the main wing forward and re-adjust the surfaces so COL and COM line up again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ihtoit","CreatedById":78942,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-23T00:41:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this is in the wrong section\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"technicalfool","CreatedById":70430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-23T01:46:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222425079\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132725\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456188102\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278942\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ihtoit\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, ihtoit said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this is in the wrong section\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably better in Tutorials, yes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice article though. Carry on!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nich","CreatedById":145678,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-23T05:19:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222425168\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132725\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456191990\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022technicalfool\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, technicalfool said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u